<p>Calcium has been found to have a positive effect in combating salinity i=
n soils. It has been shown to ameliorate the negative effects that salinity=
 has such as reduced water usage of plants.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-17" class=3D=
"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soil_salinity#cite_not=
e-17"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>17<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]=
</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Soil salinity activates <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gen=
e" title=3D"Gene">genes</a> associated with stress conditions for plants.<s=
up id=3D"cite_ref-FH_18-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Soil_salinity#cite_note-FH-18"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[<=
/span>18<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> These genes initiat=
e the production of plant stress <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/E=
nzyme" title=3D"Enzyme">enzymes</a> such as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Superoxide_dismutase" title=3D"Superoxide dismutase">superoxide d=
ismutase</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/L-ascorbate_oxidase"=
 title=3D"L-ascorbate oxidase">L-ascorbate oxidase</a>,  and Delta 1 <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DNA_polymerase" title=3D"DNA polymerase"=
>DNA polymerase</a>.  Limiting this process can be achieved by administerin=
g exogenous <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glutamine" title=3D"Gl=
utamine">glutamine</a> to plants. The decrease in the level of expression o=
f genes responsible for the synthesis of superoxide dismutase increases wit=
h the increase in glutamine concentration.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-FH_18-1" clas=
s=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soil_salinity#cite=
_note-FH-18"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>18<span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
